    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Written or spoken language that is eloquent, elegant, or ornate, particularly when expressed in terms calculated to persuade. In usage, may be intended as depreciative, referring to language characterized by artificial, insincere, or ostentatious expression; inflated or empty verbiage.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
